<doc id="1134283" wikidata="Q550643" url="?curid=1134283" title="Janusz Zarenkiewicz">
<text>Janusz Zarenkiewicz (born August 3, 1959) is a Polish former amateur boxer. He won a bronze medal in the super-heavyweight division at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where he forfeited his semi-final fight to eventual gold medalist Lennox Lewis. Zarenkiewicz also won bronze at the 1985 European Championships and was a five-time Polish national champion.

==Olympic results==
*First-round bye
*Defeated Harold Arroyo (Puerto Rico), 5–0
*Defeated Andreas Schnieders (West Germany), 3–2
*Lost to Lennox Lewis (Canada), walkover

