<doc id="1134471" wikidata="Q3987422" url="?curid=1134471" title="The Greyest of Blue Skies">
<text>The Greyest of Blue Skies is the second studio album from the Canadian rock band Finger Eleven, released in 2000. It is Finger Eleven&#x27;s first album with drummer Rich Beddoe, who replaced original drummer Rob Gommerman. The track &quot;Suffocate&quot; appeared on the film &quot;Scream 3&quot; and also in the soundtrack. The tracks &quot;First Time&quot; and &quot;Drag You Down&quot; each appeared in the &quot;Dragon Ball Z&quot; feature film Lord Slug, while the song &quot;Stay and Drown&quot; was in the &quot;Dragon Ball Z&quot; feature film Cooler&#x27;s Revenge. A contestant from &quot;Idol 2006&quot; sang &quot;Sick of It All&quot;. The album was certified Gold in Canada in June 2001.

==Track listing==
All songs written by Scott Anderson, James Black and Arnold Lanni, except for where noted.

